modules.description: Provides functions for drawing shapes, text, and images using the Cairo graphics API, including operations for setting colors, transforming coordinates, and rendering to surfaces. Works with data types such as surfaces, contexts, and paths to enable vector graphics rendering. Used to generate scalable graphics in GUI applications, export images in various formats, and integrate with GTK+ for real-time drawing.

Creates Cairo contexts for drawing on GDK drawables and provides methods to set color sources, add geometric shapes, and use pixbufs as drawing sources. Operates with Gdk.Color, Gdk.Rectangle, Gdk.region, and GdkPixbuf.pixbuf types. Enables precise rendering of images and vector graphics within GTK+ applications.
